From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 11:04:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kati: make the corpus a hard gate; pin the recent fixes with
 testcases
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The corpus runner only PRINTED its pass tally — a regression in any
kati fix was invisible unless someone compared numbers. Now
corpus_pass_rate asserts fail==0 (every non-'# TODO' case must match
GNU make) and xpass==0 (a TODO case that starts passing must be
un-TODO'd so it's enforced), keeping KATI_COMPAT_MIN as an optional
stricter floor. Filtered runs (KATI_CORPUS_ONLY) skip the gate.

New testcases pinning the recent kati work:

- sarun_selfgen_include_pattern.mk — remake-the-makefile via a PATTERN
  rule producer (the kernel's %/auto.conf → syncconfig).
- sarun_features_var.mk — .FEATURES advertises undefine /
  target-specific / order-only / second-expansion (the kernel bails
  out without 'undefine'). The standalone rkati bootstrap didn't
  advertise .FEATURES at all — brought to parity with the engine's
  embedded-make bootstrap.
- sarun_submake_makeflags_env.mk — a makefile-level
  `MAKEFLAGS += --flag` reaches a child make's ENVIRONMENT (GNU
  always exports MAKEFLAGS; the kernel's --include-dir rides this).
  Standalone rkati never exported the final MAKEFLAGS value to recipe
  children — fixed in main.rs alongside (the engine side was fixed in
  0fbfe87 and is covered by test_make_rs case 20; the standalone gap
  was found BY this testcase).
- vpath_directory_search.mk / wildcard_in_rule.mk (added with their
  fixes) are now enforced rather than advisory.

Four stale '# TODO' headers removed (err_export_override,
err_override_export, override_export, wildcard_cache) — they pass
against GNU make 4.3 today (wildcard_cache thanks to the rule-word
glob expansion), so they're armed as regressions guards now.
Tally: 374/384 pass, 10 legitimate TODOs, zero unexplained diffs.

Engine-side behaviors the standalone corpus cannot see (seed_env
MAKEFLAGS, in-box include-dir, nested-sh errexit) stay covered by
test_make_rs cases 20-22.

